## Summary

- Adds **MegaBrain Gateway** as a custom/base-URL provider in `docs/concepts/model-providers.md`
- MegaBrain is an OpenAI-compatible gateway with 500+ models across 60+ providers and `mb-auto/*` auto-routing models
- Placed in the `## Providers via models.providers (custom/base URL)` section alongside Moonshot, Volcano Engine, and other OpenAI-compatible proxies — consistent format with those entries

## Config example added

```json5
{
  agents: {
    defaults: { model: { primary: "megabrain/mb-auto/balanced" } },
  },
  models: {
    mode: "merge",
    providers: {
      megabrain: {
        baseUrl: "https://getmegabrain.com/api/gateway/v1",
        apiKey: "${MEGABRAIN_API_KEY}",
        api: "openai-completions",
        models: [
          { id: "mb-auto/balanced", name: "MB Auto Balanced" },
          { id: "mb-auto/frontier", name: "MB Auto Frontier" },
        ],
      },
    },
  },
}
```

## Test plan

- [ ] Verify the new section renders correctly in docs
- [ ] Confirm `baseUrl` endpoint returns OpenAI-compatible responses at `/chat/completions`

